                    "company": "University of Groningen",
                    "description": "Provided comprehensive support to both the Industrial Engineering and Management (IEM) educational program and the Advanced Production Engineering research group. This included designing research methodologies, techniques, and equipment for various projects, as well as training and offering technical assistance to PhD students and postdoctoral researchers. Actively facilitated industry connections and service offerings. Additionally, supervised bachelor design projects and master theses from the IEM program. \nSpearheaded the development and coordination of the elective course 'Materials Selection for Engineering Design' within the BSc IEM curriculum, focusing on the 'Production Technology and Logistics' track. Also, delivered the 'Thermochemical Diffusion Processes' segment of the 'Surface Engineering and Coating Technology' course in the MSc Mechanical Engineering curriculum, specifically catering to students pursuing the 'Materials for Mechanical Engineering' specialization.",
                    "title": "Education/Research Officer",
                    "employment_type": null
                },
                {
